a%20had%20forbidden%20Rose%20from%20contacting%20her%20teen%20daughter%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiss-colorado-arianna-lemus-resigns-in-support-of-miss-usa-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMiss%20USA%20resignation%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Voigt%20detailed%20the%20%26quot%3Bdetrimental%20mental%20and%20emotional%20toll%26quot%3B%20of%20her%20time%20as%20Miss%20USA%2C%20saying%20that%20she%20had%20been%20prescribed%20two%20anti-anxiety%20medications%20due%20to%20Rose's%20constant%20harassment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20ever%20in%20my%20life%20been%20on%20anti-anxiety%20medication%2C%26quot%3B%20Voigt%20told%20Business%20Insider%20during%20an%20interview%20in%20August%202025.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20something%20that%20came%20out%20of%20nowhere.%20It%20was%20a%20byproduct%20of%20the%20situation%20that%20we%20were%20in.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20to%20put%20on%20a%20facade%20to%20represent%20the%20organization%20because%20I%20had%20this%20title%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20agree%20with%20what%20was%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225207%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Miss%20Utah%20Noelia%20Voigt%20waves%20to%20the%20crowd%20while%20holding%20a%20bouquet%20of%20roses%20moments%20after%20being%20crowned.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651846225640b20019d7916f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMiss%20Utah%20Noelia%20Voigt%20was%20crowned%20Miss%20USA%20in%202023.%3Cp%3EMiss%20USA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Voigt%20and%20Srivastava%20reported%20Rose's%20behavior%20to%20the%20Miss%20Universe%20Organization%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20Miss%20USA%20pageant%2C%20Barbara%20and%20Jackeline%20said%20Rose%20retaliated%20by%20removing%20their%20access%20to%20the%20Miss%20USA%20and%20Miss%20Teen%20USA%20social-media%20pages%20and%20impersonating%20them%20in%20comments%20that%20praised%20her%20Miss%20USA%20leadership.%20In%20August%202024%2C%20Voigt%20and%20Srivatsava%20were%20completely%20wiped%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiss-usa-erased-noelia-voigt-umasofia-srivastava-from-social-media-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMiss%20USA%20and%20Miss%20Teen%20USA%20Instagram%20pages%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoigt%20and%20Srivastava%20weren't%20the%20only%20shocking%20resignations%20to%20hit%20Miss%20USA%20during%20Rose's%20reign.%20Multiple%20state%20pageant%20directors%20decided%20to%20leave%20the%20organization%2C%20including%20Kimberly%20Nicewonder%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Miss%20Virginia%20pageant%20for%20three%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Paula%20Miles%2C%20who%20began%20running%20pageants%20for%20Miss%20USA%20in%201979.%20Both%20women%20said%20they%20were%20resigning%20due%20to%20their%20experiences%20with%20Rose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20the%20worst%20year%20of%20our%20professional%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20Miles%2C%20who%20was%20codirector%20with%20his%20mother%2C%20Paula%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BFor%20her%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20something%20she%20built%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20lives%20she's%20changed%2C%20she%20wanted%20people's%20eyes%20to%20be%20open%20for%20what%20the%20organization%20has%20become.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236d3502e-b37e-4c85-8f83-8506c3b241e1%5C%22%3EA%20new%20era%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Miss%20USA%202024%20Alma%20Cooper%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b2714da5247369a3e9e349%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlma%20Cooper%20was%20crowned%20Miss%20USA%202024%20on%20August%204%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%3Cp%3EAlberto%20E.%20Rodriguez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBrodeur