llion%20contract%20extension%2C%20even%20though%20three%20years%20and%20%24171%20million%20still%20remained%20on%20his%20existing%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBooker's%20new%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20%2472.5%20million%20in%20annual%20average%20income%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20highest%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhighest-paid-nba-players-of-all-time-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENBA%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20keeps%20him%20in%20Phoenix%20until%20the%20summer%20of%202030%2C%20when%20he'll%20be%2034.%20It%20was%20a%20historic%20commitment%2C%20considering%20that%20Booker%20was%20still%20three%20years%20away%20from%20free%20agency%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20free%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20the%20period%20after%20a%20player's%20team%20contract%20ends%20and%20they%20can%20negotiate%20to%20sign%20with%20a%20different%20team%20%E2%80%94%20is%20typically%20a%20chance%20for%20athletes%20to%20have%20some%20control%20over%20career%20factors%20like%20location%2C%20role%2C%20and%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20players%20can%20leverage%20their%20way%20to%20better%20pay%20by%20joining%20another%20team%20or%20simply%20with%20the%20threat.%20Take%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackstone-career-path-internship-former-ny-knick-marshall-plumlee-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Knicks%3C%2Fa%3E%20forward%20OG%20Anunoby%2C%20who%20entered%20free%20agency%20last%20summer%20but%20ultimately%20signed%20a%20five-year%2C%20%24212%20million%20contract%20to%20remain%20with%20the%20Knicks%20%E2%80%94%20a%20year%20longer%20and%20%2430%20million%20more%20than%20other%20teams%20could%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20deals%20like%20Booker's%20are%20becoming%20increasingly%20common%20in%20the%20league%3B%20More%20NBA%20players%20have%20been%20forgoing%20free%20agency%20and%20signing%20extensions%20that%20rank%20among%20the%20heftiest%20in%20American%20sports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%2017%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-nba-player-mistakes-wealth-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENBA%20players%3C%2Fa%3E%20signed%20extensions%20each%20worth%20over%20%24200%20million%20in%20total%20value.%20Others%2C%20like%20Booker%2C%20have%20signed%20extensions%20worth%20less%20than%20%24200%20million%20in%20total%20value%2C%20but%20with%20average%20annual%20salaries%20topping%20%2440%20million.%20By%20comparison%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-largest-contracts-highest-paid-players-ranked%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20NFL%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20only%20have%2015%20players%20making%20%2440%20million%20or%20more%20for%20the%202026%20season%2C%20while%20MLB%20will%20have%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222971531b-7e78-4b0a-9c79-145d71e7a7aa%5C%22%3EWhy%20trades%20are%20replacing%20free%20agency%20in%20the%20NBA%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20fewer%20players%20are%20becoming%20free%20agents%2C%20why%20are%20teams%20offering%20these%20mega-extensions%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBobby%20Marks%2C%20an%20ESPN%20NBA%20salary%20cap%20analyst%20and%20a%20former%20assistant%20general%20manager%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbillionaire-joe-tsai-looks-to-launch-brooklyn-media-brand-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrooklyn%20Nets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20NBA%20incentivized%20extensions%20through%20the%20players'%20union%202023%20Collective%20Bargaining%20Agreement%2C%20which%20said%20that%20teams%20could%20offer%20extensions%20sooner%2C%20and%20player%20raises%20could%20be%20higher%20than%20in%20previous%20CBAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20teams'%20top%20players%20are%20staying%20put%20rather%20than%20hitting%20the%20open%20market%2C%20eroding%20a%20free-agency%20landscape.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D10c7ae3b8669d26397c4ed4a3681cd63c6b87453bed4059a07d3cc7bea268d1c%26postID%3D68af5569a4f7471136182cd8%26postSlug%3Dnba-players-richest-athletes-contract-extensions-breaking-free-agency-2025-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.espn.com%252Fnba%252Fstory%252F_%252Fid%252F45946735%252Fnba-free-agency-2026-preview-lebron-trae-names-storylines-watch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarks%20wrote%20for%20ESPN%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%202011-12%20to%202019-20%20seasons%2C%2041%20NBA%20veterans%20signed%20contract%20extensions.%20Since%20the%202020-21%20season%2C%20104%20players%20have%20signed%20extensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20players%20tend%20to%20take%20these%20deals%20rather%20than%20test%20the%20%26quot%3Bvolatility%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20free-agent%20market%2C%20said%20Greg%20Lawrence%2C%20an%20agent%20for%20Wasserman%20who%20helped%20Sacramento%20Kings%20center%20Domantas%20Sabonis%20secure%20a%20four-year%2C%20%24186%20million%20extension%20in%202023.%20Marks%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20lure%20of%20guaranteed%20money%20is%20so%20strong%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Marks%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ability%20to%20take%20something%20that%20you%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cycle%20has%20resulted%3A%20In%20recent%20summers%2C%20fewer%20teams%20have%20had%20salary%20cap%20space%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20of%20available%20payroll%20funds%20before%20hitting%20the%20league-mandated%20salary%20cap%20%E2%80%94%20stemming%20in%20part%20from%20COVID-impacted%20seasons.%20Less%20cap%20space%20means%20less%20cash%20for%20potential%20free-agent%20contracts%2C%20thus%20creating%20a%20push%20for%20more%20contract%20extensions%2C%20which%20take%20up%20teams'%20cap%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Lawrence%2C%20trades%20have%20somewhat%20replaced%20free%20agency.%20Teams%20tend%20to%20target%20players%20through%20trades%20instead%20of%20signing%20them%20outright%2C%20and%20players%20can%20secure%20rich%20extensions%20this%20way.%20All-Star%20point%20guard%20De'Aaron%20Fox%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20signed%20a%20four-year%2C%20%24222%20million%20extension%20with%20the%20San%20Antonio%20Spurs%20this%20summer%20after%20being%20traded%20there%20earlier%20in%20the%20year.%20He%20couldn't%20have%20signed%20as%20big%20a%20deal%20with%20San%20Antonio%20this%20summer%20as%20a%20free%20agent%2C%20according%20to%20Marks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20trend%2C%20NBA%20fans'%20focus%20has%20shifted%20from%20free-agency%20speculation%20to%20trade%20speculation%2C%20said%20Lawrence.%20But%20that's%20not%20necessarily%20trouble%20for%20the%20league%2C%20as%20a%20recent%20%2476%20billion%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frising-sports-cost-is-threat-to-hollywood-tv-budgets-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETV%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Disney%2C%20Comcast%2C%20and%20Amazon%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280779c88-3417-4f66-8109-838a953753b7%5C%22%3EHow%20a%20decrease%20in%20free%20agency%20could%20affect%20the%20NBA%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20Golden%20State%20Warriors'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdraymond-green-suspension-forces-warriors-accountability-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDraymond%20Green%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20former%20NBA%20guard%20Austin%20Rivers%20%E2%80%94%20have%20said%20that%20the%20CBA%20and%20the%20lagging%20free-agent%20market%20have%20squeezed%20out%20the%20NBA's%20%26quot%3Bmiddle%20class.%26quot%3B%20While%20many%20players%20can%20get%20rich%20extensions%2C%20remaining%20free%20agents%20often%20end%20up%20with%20shorter%20and%20smaller%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20extension%20deals%20will%20likely%20grow%2C%20said%20Marks.%20The%20NBA's%20new%20%2476%20billion%20TV%20rights%20deal%20will%20bring%20the%20league%20more%20revenue%2C%20in%20turn%20raising%20the%20salary%20cap%20and%20with%20it%2C%20player%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContracts%20that%20are%20worth%2025%25%20of%20today's%20salary%20cap%20may%20look%20like%20a%20bargain%20in%20two%20years%2C%20when%20the%20salary%20cap%20is%20higher.%20By%202028%2C%20it's%20possible%20that%20a%20star%20player%20could%20sign%20a%20five-year%20extension%20with%20a%20single-year%20salary%20worth%20over%20%24100%20million%2C%20Marks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawrence%20said%20he%20doesn't%20think%20this%20shift%20in%20player%20transactions%20has%20hurt%20the%20league%2C%20which%20has%20historically%20benefited%20from%20viewer%20attention.%20While%20Lawrence%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20July%20free-agency%20periods%20have%20been%20quieter%20than%20in%20years%20past%2C%20he%20said%20fan%20and%20media%20hype%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20new%20type%20of%20speculation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20almost%20been%20replaced%20by%20more%20of%20a%2024%2F7%20news%20cycle%20trying%20to%20predict%2C%20'When%20is%20this%20player%20going%20to%20get%20unhappy%3F'%20and%20'If%20this%20team%20starts%20the%20season%20poorly%2C%20is%20so-and-so%20going%20to%20ask%20for%20a%20trade%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20this%20year-round%20speculation%20could%20even%20be%20better%20for%20the%20league%2C%20Lawrence%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20never%20ends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnba-players-richest-athletes-contract-extensions-breaking-free-agency-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757006560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b843d7194a2d49b8af9c1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnba-players-richest-athletes-contract-extensions-breaking-free-agency-2025-9%22%2C%22summar