s%2F2025%2F09%2FBlue-and-Yellow-Modern-Business-Workshop-Facebook-Ad-2025-09-02T163022.801_11zon-1756810842-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-495313%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELittle%20Leaf%20was%20founded%20by%20Pritu%20Chaudhary%20in%202014%20in%20Varanasi%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20motivated%20by%20the%20idea%20of%20doing%20something%20meaningful%20for%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pritu%20tells%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20her%20voice%20warm%20but%20resolute.%20%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20waste%20is%20not%20just%20rubbish%3B%20it%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20create%20something%20valuable%20that%20benefits%20both%20the%20environment%20and%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20motivation%20culminated%20in%20the%20founding%20of%20Little%20Leaf%20on%202%20October%202014.%20Initially%20based%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20the%20NGO%20began%20by%20collecting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F339577%2Fhyderabad-abhishek-agarwal-goodeebag-free-waste-recycling-service%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaste%20paper%20from%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20handing%20it%20over%20to%20recycling%20companies.%20Soon%2C%20however%2C%20the%20idea%20evolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritu%20discovered%20manufacturers%20who%20could%20turn%20recycled%20paper%20into%20notebooks.%20Seeing%20an%20opportunity%20to%20close%20the%20loop%2C%20she%20envisioned%20a%20system%20where%20waste%20paper%20could%20be%20collected%2C%20recycled%2C%20and%20converted%20into%20notebooks%20for%20children%20who%20otherwise%20could%20not%20afford%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20humble%20beginning%20with%20the%20strength%20to%20change%20many%20futures%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELittle%20Leaf%20does%20not%20directly%20recycle%20paper%20or%20manufacture%20notebooks.%20Ins